Diagram 1 (Pae)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par White's cut at 1 is comes to mind first. Of course, black capturing white at 2 is the strongest response. White can only play 3 and black cuts at 4 creating a pae.
\par
\par In this case, a pae is a failure. There is a move to capture black unconditionally.
\par
\par }
