Diagram 3 (Correct)
[{\rtf1\ansi\ansicpg949\deff0{\fonttbl{\f0\fnil\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}{\f1\fmodern\fprq2\fcharset129 \'b1\'bc\'b8\'b2;}}
\viewkind4\uc1\pard\lang1042\f0\fs18
\par It is clever for white to play dansu with 1. Please note that this is the 2-1 point.
\par
\par Black can do no more than capture with 2. Then, white plays dansu with 3, finishing black off. Black is left with a dead shape.
\par
\par \pard\nowidctlpar\qj Instead of 2, if black plays \b\f1 A\b0\f0 , white plays at 3 and there is no way for black to live.
\par }
